<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="411" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="21.[1367,2573,720,1658]" pageId="21" pageNumber="411">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1369,1730,1433,1462]" pageId="21" pageNumber="411">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
CITES Appendix II. Classified as Data Deficient on The IUCN Red Lust (as 
<taxonomicName box="[1616,1759,1468,1501]" class="Mammalia" family="Cebidae" genus="Cebus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Primates" pageId="21" pageNumber="412" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="albifrons">C. albifrons</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hershkovitz" authorityYear="1949" box="[1768,1861,1468,1501]" class="Mammalia" family="Cebidae" genus="Cebus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Primates" pageId="21" pageNumber="411" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cesarae">cesarae</taxonomicName>
). The Rio Cesar White-fronted Capuchin occurs in Ciénaga Grande de Santa Marta and Los Flamencos fauna and flora sanctuaries, and probably also in Macuira National Natural Park.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
